The correct way to start a conversation with the model **"mistral-medium-latest"** using the TypeScript client is shown in **[1] Conversations**:

```typescript
let response = await client.beta.conversations.start({
    model: "mistral-medium-latest",
    inputs:[{role: "user", content:"Who is Albert Einstein?"}]
});
```

The required parameter for specifying the starting point when restarting a conversation stream in TypeScript is `fromEntryId`.

This is shown in the example under **[3] Conversations (cont.) (cont.) (cont.)** (TypeScript restart tab):
```typescript
let stream = await client.beta.conversations.restartStream({
    conversationId: conversation.conversationId,
    conversationRestartStreamRequest: {
        fromEntryId: conversationMessages.messages[conversationMessages.messages.length - 1].id?.toString() || '',
        inputs: "Who is albert Enstein?"
    }
});
```

